  <prompt>
    Execute the A-5a verification spike (FR-05 verify phase). Per OC-R4-02, the R3 UQ-03 verification said tabs persist; recent operator feedback contradicts that finding. Verify-then-fix protocol: this task is VERIFICATION ONLY. Do NOT remediate. Answer five questions with operator-observable evidence: (1) Do tabs persist across browser REFRESH today? (2) Do tabs persist across browser CLOSE/REOPEN today? (3) On reopen, does the active tab default to Home, last-active, or something else? (4) Where is state stored — sessionStorage, localStorage, BFF, Cosmos? (5) Is the spec/UX expectation that browser-reopen → Home tab? Publish to `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/tab-persistence-verification-2026-05.md`. Task 031 is BLOCKED until this memo lands.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend investigator with React 19 + browser-storage familiarity (sessionStorage vs localStorage, BFF/Cosmos write-through from R2 D-06). Reads code AND probes browser behavior — does not infer from code alone.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Verification memo at `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/tab-persistence-verification-2026-05.md` answering the five questions with: (a) code evidence (file:line citations for the persistence layer) and (b) operator-observable smoke evidence (refresh + close/reopen). Concludes with the operator-confirmed "actually broken gap" — the acceptance target for 031.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      R3 task 065 implemented `SessionPersistenceService` extension with workspace tabs[] write-through to Cosmos via BFF (`PATCH/GET /ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/tabs`). R3 task 063 marked NFR-09 satisfied. OC-R4-02 records operator feedback contradicting that finding — original verification likely measured refresh-within-session but NOT close/reopen across browser sessions.

      Stack (from existing code): `WorkspaceTabManager.ts` (in-memory + serialize/restore methods); `WorkspacePane.tsx` (debounced PATCH on mutation, GET on mount); BFF `SessionPersistenceService` persists to Cosmos with `/tenantId` partition key. `chatSessionId` comes from `useAiSession()` — its lifetime is the key open question (sessionStorage = refresh-only; localStorage = close-survives; auth-derived = depends on token cache).

      Verify-then-fix is non-negotiable per CLAUDE.md §1 / OC-R4-02. Do NOT pre-build a fix.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceTabManager.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspacePane.tsx</file>
