  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Locate R3 prior verification">Glob `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/*tab*`, `*nfr-09*`, `*backwards-compat*`. Read R3 memo(s); extract scenarios tested, evidence captured, whether close/reopen was distinguished from refresh.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Read persistence stack">Read `WorkspaceTabManager.ts` (focus on serialize/restore) and `WorkspacePane.tsx` (focus on PATCH/GET effects + chatSessionId dependency). Capture where chatSessionId comes from and what happens when it's missing on mount.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Trace chatSessionId lifetime">Grep for `chatSessionId`, `setChatSessionId`, the `useAiSession` implementation. Determine: does the id survive browser CLOSE? (Check storage type: sessionStorage / localStorage / auth-derived.)</step>
    <step order="4" name="Identify storage ground truth">Grep `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/` and `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/` for `sessionStorage`, `localStorage`, `IndexedDB`. Cross-reference with BFF Cosmos persistence — confirm tabs themselves live in Cosmos, but the lookup KEY (chatSessionId) is what determines survival.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Operator smoke — refresh">Either via `ui-test` skill or operator-driven: (1) open SpaarkeAi; (2) open 3 non-Home tabs via Context wizards; (3) refresh (Ctrl+R); (4) observe — do all 3 tabs return? Which tab is active? Capture PASS/FAIL/PARTIAL with screenshot or trace.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Operator smoke — close/reopen">Same setup. Then: (1) CLOSE the entire browser process; (2) reopen browser, navigate to SpaarkeAi; (3) observe — do tabs return? Active tab Home or last-active? Capture result. THIS IS THE SCENARIO OC-R4-02 SAYS WAS MISSED IN R3.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Document spec expectation">Read FR-05 in `spec.md` and OC-R4-02 in `plan.original.md`. Document expectation: "browser-reopen restores tabs" OR "browser-reopen defaults to Home"? If ambiguous, flag as open question.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Synthesize the actually-broken gap">Cross-reference actual behavior (steps 5+6) vs spec expectation (step 7). Identify the delta. Possible gaps: sessionStorage→localStorage migration needed / BFF session-id stability needed / default-active-tab logic needs correction / no gap exists (R3 was correct).</step>
    <step order="9" name="Write verification memo">Create the memo with: header (date, scope, investigator); Q1-Q5 answers with code citations + smoke evidence; actually-broken gap section (synthesized delta); recommendation for task 031 (which of three paths, with rationale); open questions for operator.</step>
    <step order="10" name="Verify + update TASK-INDEX">No code changed, no build. Update TASK-INDEX.md row 030 → ✅ completed. Add note pointing to memo + recommended fix path. If memo concludes "no gap — R3 was correct," surface to operator before 031 runs (031 may be downscoped or cancelled).</step>
    <step order="11" name="Document deviations">If any deviation (browser smoke unavailable, scope expanded, additional storage layers discovered), document in `notes/` alongside the memo.</step>
  </steps>

